Documenting & Publishing API’s & e-commerce app API’s

Swagger Petstore  – it is an API  site you have lots of API for testing with example

We are creating some example in swagger

Create User
1>Open PostMan
2>Create one new collection and name it as Swagger Petstore
3>create a new request and name it as create user
4>now select POST and paste this URL: https://petstore.swagger.io/v2/user
5>now in the body select raw and select JSON and past this script
{
    "id":{{id}},
    "username":"{{username}}",
    "firstName":"{{firstName}}",
    "lastName":"{{lastName}}",
    "email":"{{email}}",
    "password":"{{password}}",
    "phone":"{{phone}}",
    "userStatus":"{{userStatus}}"

}
6>now go pre-script and paste this script
const randomnum = Math.floor((Math.random()*100+1));
var randomstr = "john"+Math.random().toString(36).substring(2);

pm.environment.set("id",randomnum);
pm.collectionVariables.set("username",randomstr);
pm.collectionVariables.set("firstName",randomstr);
pm.collectionVariables.set("lastName",randomstr);
pm.collectionVariables.set("email",randomstr+"gmail.com");
pm.collectionVariables.set("password",randomstr);
pm.collectionVariables.set("phone","1111111");
pm.collectionVariables.set("userStatus",0);
//console.log(randomnum);
7>now go to post script and paste this script
pm.test("check status code",function(){
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});

Get User By name
1>Open Postman
2>create a new request and name it as Get User By Name
3>now select GET and paste this URL: https://petstore.swagger.io/v2/user/{{firstName}}
4>now in the post script paste the below script
pm.test("check status code", function(){
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});


Updated User
1>Open Postman
2>create a new request and name it as Updated User
3>now select PUT and paste this URL: https://petstore.swagger.io/v2/user/{{firstName}}
4>now in the body select raw and select JSON and paste this script
{
    "id":{{id}},
    "username":"{{username}}",
    "firstName":"{{firstName}}",
    "lastName":"{{lastName}}",
    "email":"{{email}}",
    "password":"{{password}}",
    "phone":"{{phone}}",
    "userStatus":"{{userStatus}}"
}
5>now in the pre-request paste this script
var randomstr = "john"+Math.random().toString(36).substring(2);

//updating email & phone
pm.collectionVariables.set("email",randomstr+"@gmail.com");
pm.collectionVariables.set("phone","22222222");
6>now in the post request paste this script
pm.test("check status code",function(){
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});

Delete User
1>Open postman
2>create new request and name it as Delete User
3>now select DELETE and paste this UR: https://petstore.swagger.io/v2/user/{{firstName}}
4>now in the post request paste this script
pm.test("check status code", function(){
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});

pm.environment.unset("id");
pm.environment.unset("username");
pm.environment.unset("firstName");
pm.environment.unset("lastName");
pm.environment.unset("email");
pm.environment.unset("password");
pm.environment.unset("phone");
pm.environment.unset("userStatus");

Now run the collection and check the console and response.

Now Create and Publish documentation
1>Select the collection and click on View Complete Documentation
2>Click on Publish
3>Click on Publish
4>Copy the Published Documentation URL 
https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/46579071/2sBXihoraA
5>Now share with your friends
6>They can open this URL and click on Run In Postman
7>Now select the workspace and import the collection
8>It will show you everything which we have created above.

Ecommerce Applications

Opencart – it is a free ecommerce API application

Opencart Build Deployment / installation
1)Opencart download location:
https://www.opencart.com/index.php?route=cms/download

2)XAMPP for apache, mysql, and php installation
https://www.apachefriends.org/download.html

3>Once the XAMPP installation is completed
4>Open the XAMPP Control Panel
5>Now start Apache and MySQL

Step by step OpenCart Installation

6>Copy opencart folder(step1)in the below location.
C:\xampp\htdocs

7>After copying rename the folder “opencart”

8>Rename files
Go to c:\xampp\htdocs\opencart\upload
Rename file ‘config-dist.php’ to ‘config.php’

Go to c:\xampp\htdocs\opencart\upload\admin
Rename file ‘config-dist.php’ to ‘config.php’

9>Connect to the database and create DB.
DB Access URL : http://localhost/phpMyAdmin/

Create new database ‘openshop’ 
1>Go to the database section
2>Provide the database name as openshop
3>select type as collection and click on create

10>Open the site http://localhost/opencart/
Click on Upload
11>click on continue 

If you are getting above error GD is off then you have to do below steps.
Open XAMPP control panel, click on config button for Apache then open PHP(php.ini) file
Add new entry in the php.ini file extension=gd
Then stop and start Apache server. Then you will see below screen.

12>Provide the database connection details
1.	Please enter your database connection details
	DB Driver : MySQL
	Hostname : localhost
	Username: root
	Database: openshop
	Port:3306
2.	Please enter a username and password for the administrator
Username : admin
Password: admin
Email: admin@gmail.com
3.	Click on continue

13>Go to location c:\xampp\htdocs\opencart\upload
Delete install folder

14>Go to Application URL
Frontend application URL : http://localhost/opencart/upload/

15>Now open the opencart in the browser
16>login with credentials
17>go to user section under user
18>add new user and generate API Token and Status enabled
19>Now go to Ip address tab and add your computer ip address
20>now click on save.

